cs.CL, cs.FL, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.IT

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the use of RNNs in natural language processing applications. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is also likely as the paper investigates the computational complexity of recognizing weighted languages using RNNs. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as RNNs are a type of machine learning model. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper discusses the computational complexity of various problems related to RNNs. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper deals with the determination of the highest-weighted string in RNNs, which can be seen as an information-theoretic problem.
